\f0\b\fs28 Signal Definitions\

\f1\b0\fs24 All signals referenced in the entry and regime sections are computed from SPY daily data (unless noted otherwise), sourced from the ORATS historical chain plus spot close. Definitions are listed here so rules can be implemented unambiguously by the user or any future tool.\
\
\b SPY VRP (volatility risk premium)\b0\
\
\'95  VRP = ATM IV30 \'96 RV20\
\'95  ATM IV30 = 30-DTE at-the-money implied volatility, interpolated from SPY chain to exactly 30 days\
\'95  RV20 = 20-trading-day realized volatility of SPY close-to-close log returns, annualized (sqrt(252) scale)\
\'95  "VRP positive" = VRP > 0 (implied is pricing a cushion over recent realized)\
\'95  "VRP negative" = VRP < 0 (realized already exceeds implied)\
\
\b SPY term structure spread\b0\
\
\'95  Term spread = front 30-DTE ATM IV \'96 back 75-DTE ATM IV\
\'95  "Contango" = term spread < 0 (back > front, the normal condition)\
\'95  "Inverted" = term spread > 0 (front > back, vol regime stress)\
\'95  "Near-inverted" = term spread within a small positive band (used only where the signal-study memo invokes it)\
\
\b SPY 252-day IV rank\b0\
\
\'95  IV rank = (current ATM IV30 \'96 252d min ATM IV30) / (252d max ATM IV30 \'96 252d min ATM IV30)\
\'95  Range [0, 1]. Recomputed daily on a rolling 252-trading-day window\
\'95  Thresholds used in this plan: 0.5 (bear_call H1 gate), 0.7 (bull_put soft-downsize), 0.9 (high-conviction signal study comparison)\
\
\b SPY 200-day and 50-day moving averages\b0\
\
\'95  Simple moving average of SPY daily close over 200 and 50 trading days\
\'95  "SPY < 200dma" evaluated at the entry day\'92s close\
\'95  "SPY > +X% over 200dma" = (close \'96 200dma) / 200dma > X / 100\
\
\b Max pain strike\b0\
\
\'95  MP = argmin over strikes K of \uc0\u8721  over strikes Ks of cOI(Ks) \'b7 max(0, K \'96 Ks) + pOI(Ks) \'b7 max(0, Ks \'96 K)\
\'95  Uses open interest at the chain snapshot referenced by the window: T-5 for Window B entry decisions, T-1 for the pin-reliability scan\
\
\b Extension above MP\b0\
\
\'95  Extension = (spot \'96 MP) / MP\
\'95  Positive = spot above MP; negative = spot below MP\
\'95  Used for aggressive bear_call_mp analysis (Phase 2h)\
\

\f0\b\fs28 Structures & Entry Rules\

\f0\b\fs26 Bull Put Vertical\

\f1\b0\fs24 A bull put vertical is a defined-risk credit spread: short put at a higher strike, long put at a lower strike on the same expiration. It profits if the underlying stays above the short strike at exit.\
\
\b Signals that favor a bull put entry\b0\
\
\'95  SPY term structure in contango \'97 front-month ATM IV < back-month ATM IV\
\'95  SPY VRP positive \'97 IV30 - RV20 > 0 (implied is pricing a premium over recent realized)\
\'95  Both conditions required jointly \'97 approximately 57% of historical T-5 entry days qualify (742 of 1,307 cycles in the Phase 2f test)\
\'95  When either fails, skip the entry; the lift disappears\
\'95  Do not use the inverse rule "skip inverted days." The validated rule is specifically \i require contango AND VRP>0\i0\
\
\b Generally optimal construction\b0\
\
\'95  \b Window A (45-DTE managed):\b0  30-delta short put, long put one wing width lower (~0.5% of spot, floor $2). Exit on first trigger of 50% of max profit or 21 DTE.\
\'95  \b Window B (near-OpEx):\b0  T-5 entry. Short put at the strike nearest max-pain; long put one strike lower. Requires spot at or above MP at entry. Held to expiration \'97 no early exit.\
\'95  Size by dollar risk, not contract count. One SPX contract is roughly 100x one XLU contract in dollar terms.\
\'95  Enter at mid-or-better; a half-spread of slippage wipes out most of the edge.\
\
\b Symbols that respond well (personality)\b0\
\
\'95  Blue-chip premium-selling tier \'97 high aggregate OI, deep weekly-expiration chains, moderate implied vol (~17-34%), modest VRP\
\'95  Liquidity is non-negotiable \'97 OI at least 10K on relevant strikes, bid-ask at most 10% of mid on both legs\
\'95  Directional profile: upward drift or range-bound \'97 the implicit bet is "short side near-OTM rarely tested"\
\'95  No binary earnings inside the DTE window \'97 earnings moves are bimodal and break the carry thesis\
\'95  Validated shortlist at realistic friction, managed exit: see COHORT_BULL_PUT in gate_config.py. Selection criteria: 73-88% win rate, +$0.01 to +$0.13 mean per cycle, 71-92% year consistency across 13 years. Detail memory: project_per_symbol_bullput_shortlist.md.\
\'95  Highest-conviction tier \'97 names with year-over-year consistency above 85% across the 13-year sample. The qualifier does not currently distinguish this sub-tier in code; it is descriptive guidance for sizing intuition and review priority.\
\
\b Symbols that do NOT respond well\b0\
\
\'95  Commodity and macro-flow-driven names \'97 metals miners (NEM, GDX, FCX), energy cyclicals; dealer gamma is overwhelmed by macro flow\
\'95  Binary-event names \'97 biotech baskets (XBI), single-name pharma with FDA calendars, active M&A targets\
\'95  Vol-toys and leveraged/inverse products \'97 VXX, TLRY, LCID, RIVN, HOOD, ARKK, TEVA, EWZ\
\'95  Rate/duration-sensitive ETFs \'97 TLT is macro-directional, not pinning-driven\
\'95  Negative-VRP names where realized vol persistently exceeds implied \'97 no cushion to harvest\
\
\b Macro (SPX as proxy)\b0\
\
\'95  \b Favorable:\b0  SPX above 200dma, term structure in contango, VRP positive, VIX moderate, no active geopolitical shock\
\'95  \b Unfavorable:\b0  SPX below 200dma, term inverted, VRP negative, VIX elevated, confirmed bear trend\
\'95  Regime sensitivity is total. In backtested bear windows (COVID 2020, 2022 inflation, Dec 2018, Aug 2015), bull_put mean flips from modest positive to meaningfully negative (-$0.18 to -$0.40 per cycle). The structure\'92s edge is at least partly a bull-market artifact of a 14-year regime-dominant backtest.\
\'95  Treat the SPX regime check as a gate. Running bull_put heavy into a confirmed bear regime is quantifiably expensive.\
\
\b Rolling (validated)\b0\
\
\'95  \b Trigger:\b0  MTM loss at or beyond 1x entry credit\
\'95  \b Style:\b0  down-and-out \'97 close the losing position, open a fresh bull_put at the new max-pain strike on the next monthly OpEx\
\'95  \b Net-credit requirement:\b0  the roll must open for a credit; otherwise accept the loss\
\'95  \b Cap:\b0  one roll per original cycle; serial rolling is untested\
\'95  \b Per-name selectivity:\b0  SPX, WMT, DIA, VNQ, QQQ, TLT, SPY benefit from rolling. XLU, IYR, XLV, KO do not \'97 hold to expiry on these names\
\'95  Do not gate the roll decision by signal filter. The contango+VRP>0 rule is an entry signal; at trigger day it destroys edge\
\'95  Do not use spot-based stops \'97 short puts mean-revert enough that intraweek breach is not a reliable exit trigger\
\
\b Expected outcomes (at realistic retail friction)\b0\
\
\'95  Win rate: approximately 70-80% on curated names; 87% on the signal-filtered MP-anchored Window B variant\
\'95  Mean P&L: +$0.05 to +$0.13 per cycle on the 12-name shortlist; +$0.019 per cycle on signal-filtered Window B\
\'95  Tail: worst cohort cycle roughly -$6 per contract held to expiry; rolling widens the 1st-percentile drawdown to approximately -$2.50 while improving the mean\
\'95  Expect long stretches of small consistent winners punctuated by occasional larger losers. Size for the tail, not the mean.\
\
\b Per-ticker moneyness (VALIDATED 2026-05-02)\b0\
\
The 30-delta short put is a universe-wide default, but per-ticker walk-forward testing of three moneyness specs (OTM 0.30\uc0\u916 , ATM 0.50\u916 , ITM 0.70\u916 ) on the 162-ticker ORATS universe (45-DTE, slip=0.50, managed-50%, train \u8804 2022, val 2023+) produced 36 names where a non-default short delta is statistically validated in BOTH train and val windows (paired-direction p<0.05 both halves). 28 of those promote to ATM (\u916 0.50); 8 promote to ITM (\u916 0.70). The remaining 126 names default to OTM. Universe-level paired Wilcoxon under Bonferroni: ATM > OTM (median diff +0.225, p<0.0001), ITM > ATM (+0.258, p<0.0001), ITM > OTM (+0.397, p=0.002). Cluster-2 ungated/gated cells: ITM strongest (+$0.115/cycle gated, ATM +$0.104, OTM +$0.021).\
\
The lookup is operationally enforced at trade-construction time: scripts/monitor/moneyness_lookup.py recommended_short_delta(ticker, "bull_put", exit_rule="mgd50") reads data/profile/bull_put_moneyness_recommendation.parquet and overrides scripts/backtest/config.py:VERTICAL_SHORT_DELTA before each construction-block render. Daily-alert rows annotate the choice inline with the train/val p-values and sample sizes that earned the promotion. Default short delta when no walk-forward evidence: 0.30 (OTM). Pre-reg: docs/BULL_PUT_MONEYNESS_PREREG.md. Detail memory: project_per_ticker_moneyness_studies.md.\
\
\b Pending investigations (not part of validated plan)\b0\
\
\'95  \b RSI-14 bullish divergence as entry confirmation.\b0  Tested 2026-04-24: SPY at 20-day low with RSI-14 NOT at 20-day low precedes forward 25-day return of +4.71% vs +1.24% baseline (~4x lift, N=109). Asymmetric finding \'97 bullish divergence works as a BUY signal from oversold conditions; bearish divergence does NOT work as a sell signal. Candidate entry confirmation for bull_put on pullbacks; not yet promoted because the lift is documented on forward SPY return, not on bull_put cycle P&L directly. Needs a dedicated cycle-level test before becoming a validated entry gate.\
\'95  \b Full Mag 7 breadth divergence.\b0  Mag 4 (AAPL/MSFT/META/TSLA) divergence vs SPY showed a modest negative effect on thin sample (fwd 25d +0.79% vs +1.41% baseline, N=109). Cannot confirm or rule out the broader published finding until AMZN/GOOGL/NVDA ORATS data is ingested.\
\

\f0\b\fs26 Bear Call Vertical\

\f1\b0\fs24 A bear call vertical is a defined-risk credit spread: short call at a lower strike, long call at a higher strike on the same expiration. It profits if the underlying stays below the short strike at exit. Bear call is the regime mirror of bull put: its edge lives almost entirely in confirmed bear regimes. In bull-regime-dominated data, cohort-wide bear_call is not a standalone trade.\
\
\b Signals that favor a bear call entry\b0\
\
\'95  \b Primary (validated H1 filter, 2026-04-24):\b0  SPY below 200-day moving average AND SPY 252-day IV rank > 0.5. Lifts aggressive bear_call_mp from -$0.087 baseline to +$0.092/cycle (40% win rate, N=102 over 13 years). This is the only validated bear_call entry gate.\
\'95  \b Surprising negative finding:\b0  term structure inversion alone is DIS-informative for bear_call. Adding "term inverted" to the regime filter HURTS performance (-$0.152 in the SPY<200dma+term-inv cohort). The symmetric-opposite-of-bull_put hypothesis is falsified.\
\'95  In bull regimes (SPY above 200dma), no validated signal makes standalone bear_call profitable. Default posture is "do not enter."\
\'95  Entry conditions based on spot-extension-above-MP (spot >5% above MP, mean-reverter cohort filter) have been tested in Phase 2h and do NOT confer edge on their own.\
\'95  The H1 filter fires on roughly 4% of historical trading days. Bear_call is an occasional trade, not a persistent book.\
\
\b Generally optimal construction\b0\
\
\'95  \b Window A (45-DTE managed):\b0  30-delta short call, long call one wing width higher (~0.5% of spot, floor $2). Exit on first trigger of 50% of max profit or 21 DTE.\
\'95  \b Window B (near-OpEx, T-5 entry, held to expiry):\b0  30-delta short call, long call one strike higher. Marginal to negative in bull regimes; flips positive in bear windows.\
\'95  \b MP-anchoring does not lift bear_call.\b0  Tested directly in Phase 2c: short call at strike nearest MP versus short call at 30-delta produced no edge lift. The asymmetric finding \'97 MP-anchoring helps puts, not calls \'97 is load-bearing.\
\'95  \b Aggressive ITM MP-anchored variant (spot above MP entry) does not work standalone.\b0  Tested in Phase 2h across 2,686 cycles at four extension thresholds (0-2%, 2-5%, 5-10%, >=10%): every bucket negative, cohort mean -$0.087/cycle, win rate 21.7%. Do NOT deploy outside a confirmed bear regime gate.\
\'95  Size by dollar risk; 1-wide wings on high-priced underlyings are particularly slippage-sensitive.\
\
\b Symbols that respond well (personality)\b0\
\
