\f0\b\fs26 Inverted Fly\

\f1\b0\fs24 An inverted fly is a four-leg defined-risk long-volatility structure: long 1 ATM call + long 1 ATM put (forming an ATM straddle body) + short 1 OTM call + short 1 OTM put (the short wings). All four legs on the same expiration and underlying. Net debit paid at entry. The position profits when the underlying moves past either short strike by exit. Maximum loss = the debit paid, realized if the underlying pins at or near spot and all four legs expire at their starting-strike intrinsic. Maximum profit = (wing width \'d7 100) \'96 entry debit, realized if the underlying closes at or beyond either wing strike. \i Spot\i0  throughout this section means the current underlying price at entry. All tested results use \i slip=0.25\i0  (each leg fills 0.25 \'d7 bid-ask-half-spread away from the midpoint) as the realistic-retail friction assumption.\
\
Unlike the three short-premium structures above, inverted fly is a long-volatility bet. It pays when realized moves exceed the implied vol priced at entry. Structurally it is the regime counterpart to bull_put and bear_call \'97 running inverted_fly alongside a bull_put on the same name produces a natural regime hedge: when the premium-seller wings test, the inverted fly pays. This structure requires wide wings: narrower than 5% of spot produces a degenerate long-ATM-with-decoration that decays to zero. Validated wing width is 10% of spot.\
\
\b Signals that favor entry (TESTED \'97 VALIDATED)\b0\
\
\'95  \b SPY term_spread > 0 (inverted term structure).\b0  Primary validated gate (Phase A IF batch, 2026-04-24). Lifts universe-wide mean from +$0.191/cycle (all cycles) to +$0.639/cycle on term-inverted days only. Win rate lifts from 60.2% to 66.6%. Fires on ~20% of historical trading days.\
\'95  \b Joint stack: term inverted AND SPY 252-day IV rank > 0.5.\b0  Mean +$0.697/cycle (N=1,975, 66.9% win). Highest-conviction cohort.\
\'95  \b Joint stack: term inverted AND SPY VRP < 0.\b0  Mean +$0.656/cycle (N=1,613, 67.5% win). Alternate joint-stress gate.\
\'95  \b Do NOT enter on contango + VRP>0 days.\b0  That is the Phase 2f bull_put entry signal. Applied to inverted_fly it ACTIVELY HURTS (filter lift \'96$0.086/cycle). The two structures are entry-gate opposites. When the bull_put book is deploying, the inverted_fly book should be skipping.\
\'95  \b Do NOT use IV rank > 0.7 alone.\b0  Tested and essentially zero lift (N=937, mean +$0.185, lift \'96$0.006). The market has already priced the move into the ATM straddle; the body is too expensive. IV rank > 0.5 is the usable threshold \'97 less extreme, catches the sweet spot.\
\
\b Trade mechanics \'97 tested entry/exit rules\b0\
\
\'95  \b 45-day entry rule (VALIDATED).\b0  Enter at approximately 45 days to expiration. Long 1 ATM call + long 1 ATM put (straddle body). Short 1 OTM call at strike approximately spot \'d7 1.10. Short 1 OTM put at strike approximately spot \'d7 0.90. Wings scaled to 10% of spot on each side.\
\'95  \b Exit rule (VALIDATED): 50% of maximum profit, else held to expiration.\b0  Close the position when unrealized gain reaches 50% of maximum profit. Otherwise hold to expiration and let the wings settle at intrinsic. \b NO 21-day time stop.\b0  Tested and it DESTROYS long-vol edge: universe-wide 50%-only +$0.191/cycle vs managed first-trigger (50%/21-DTE) \'96$0.004/cycle. The 21-DTE time stop exits before the bulk of long-vol payoffs, which concentrate in the final two weeks when the underlying actually moves.\
\'95  \b Near-OpEx (T-5) entry FAILS (TESTED, REJECTED).\b0  Mean +$0.041/cycle, negative median, 5\'d7 weaker than 45-DTE. Additionally the term-inversion gate that LIFTS 45-DTE entry ACTIVELY HURTS at T-5 (\'96$0.190/cycle filtered). Same signal, opposite effect based on time-to-expiration. Do NOT use T-5 entry for inverted_fly.\
\'95  \b Wing width: 10% of spot (VALIDATED).\b0  Tested at 3%, 5%, 10%, 15% of spot. 10% is the sweet spot \'97 universe-wide mean +$0.146/cycle; cluster 2 at 10% wings has genuine year-round edge (+$0.167 non-crash, +$1.30 in crashes). 15% wings match 10% on mean but go slightly NEGATIVE in Volmageddon 2018. Narrower than 5% degenerates to an ATM-straddle-with-decoration.\
\'95  \b Sizing.\b0  By dollar debit per contract (entry cost = max loss). SPX inverted fly at 10% wings is typically $1,500\'96$3,000 debit per contract; AMD or CAR is $400\'96$900 per contract. Naive per-contract sizing overweights index names by 5\'96 10\'d7. SPX alone carries 77% of pair book dollar P&L; sizing must account for this.\
\'95  \b Execution.\b0  Open all four legs simultaneously on a combo ticket. Legging in during inverted term structure risks paying more on later legs as IV continues rising.\
\
\b Per-ticker wing width (VALIDATED 2026-05-02)\b0\
\
The 10%-of-spot wing width above is the universe-level finding from the wide-wings study. Per-ticker walk-forward testing of four wing specs (narrow_2pct, medium_5pct, wide_10pct, vwide_15pct) on the 162-ticker ORATS universe (45-DTE, 50%-only exit, train \uc0\u8804 2022, val 2023+, both halves p<0.05 same direction) refines this:\
\
\'95  \b 7 tickers \uc0\u8594  wide_10pct\b0  (broad indices and dividend stalwarts \'97 names whose realized-move distribution rewards the wider short strikes).\
\'95  \b 7 tickers \uc0\u8594  medium_5pct\b0  (Mag-7-class single names and high-vol cyclicals \'97 5% wings capture the typical move while keeping debit small enough that the structure pays back at moderate magnitude).\
\'95  \b 2 tickers \uc0\u8594  narrow_2pct\b0  (rare; specific underliers where 2% captures the typical 45-day move).\
\'95  \b 0 tickers \uc0\u8594  vwide_15pct.\b0  15% wings never survive walk-forward; 10% is the practical maximum.\
\'95  \b 146 tickers default to medium_5pct\b0  in the absence of walk-forward evidence. This is the new fallback (the prior scripts/backtest/config.py:BFLY_WING_PCT_SPOT_V2 = 0.0025 default was much too narrow \'97 a degenerate ATM-straddle-with-decoration). Universe-level managed mean: wide_10pct +$0.12, medium_5pct positive, narrow_2pct \'96$0.12. Under the IF gate (term inverted, ~20% of cycles), wide_10pct lifts to +$0.49/cycle.\
\
The lookup is operationally enforced at trade-construction time: scripts/monitor/moneyness_lookup.py recommended_if_wing(ticker) reads data/profile/inverted_fly_wing_recommendation.parquet and overrides scripts/backtest/config.py:BFLY_WING_PCT_SPOT before each construction-block render. The text "10% of spot" elsewhere in this section remains the canonical universe-level wing for narrative purposes; the per-ticker lookup is the deployable spec. Detail memory: project_per_ticker_moneyness_studies.md.\
