\f0\b\fs26 ZEBRA (Zero Extrinsic Back Ratio)\
\
\f1\b0\fs24 A ZEBRA is a 3-contract single-underlying structure designed to replicate long stock exposure with negligible time decay. Buy 2\'d7 ITM call at ~70\uc0\u916  + sell 1\'d7 ATM call at ~50\uc0\u916 . All three legs share the same expiration. Net debit at entry. Defined risk: max loss = the debit, realized only if spot expires below the long-call strike. The structural property: when the extrinsic value collected from the short ATM call is at least equal to the total extrinsic paid for the two long ITM calls, the position has zero (or positive) net theta and time passes without bleeding the position. Net delta at entry is approximately +0.90 to +1.15, comparable to long stock with slight upward leverage from the practitioner search.\
\
Pre-registered and tested 2026-04-25 (docs/ZEBRA_PREREG.md). All four pre-reg hypotheses pass at slip=0.50: extrinsic-rule fire rate ~95%, flat-day MTM mean +$0.58/day (no theta drag, in fact slightly positive), median upside capture ratio 1.152 (BEATS long stock on upside cycles), capital efficiency 0.21 (debit is 21% of stock cost). Walk-forward validates on 13 of 13 top cohort names. Detail: project_zebra_findings.md.\
\
\b Why this fits the plan\b0\
\
\'95  Defined-risk by construction (max loss = debit), policy-compliant.\
\'95  Long-stock-equivalent with capped downside \'97 reduces capital-at-risk versus owning shares while preserving (and slightly leveraging) upside.\
\'95  Different cadence (75-DTE) and different deployment thesis (high-conviction directional) from the credit-spread book \'97 fills a real gap.\
\'95  Mean P&L beats long stock on the deployable cohort 2.13\'d7 in the historical sample.\
\
\b Trade mechanics \'97 tested entry/exit rules\b0\
\
\'95  \b Entry (VALIDATED).\b0  ~75 calendar days to expiration on a monthly OpEx; snap to nearest trading day. Buy 2\'d7 long call at ~70\uc0\u916 ; sell 1\'d7 short call at ~50\uc0\u916  (ATM). Same expiration.\
\'95  \b Practitioner construction (VALIDATED).\b0  In every cycle, search ITM call strikes from 0.55\uc0\u916  to 0.90\uc0\u916  and pick the candidate closest to 0.70\uc0\u916  whose extrinsic value satisfies short_extrinsic \uc0\u8805  2\'d7 long_extrinsic. The literal 70/50 spec satisfies this rule on only some cycles; the practitioner search satisfies it on ~95%. If no candidate satisfies the rule on a given chain, skip the cycle.\
\'95  \b Pre-flight check.\b0  At entry, compute (short_extrinsic \'96 2\'d7 long_extrinsic). This is the extrinsic cushion. Must be \uc0\u8805  $0 or do not open.\
\'95  \b Exit (VALIDATED).\b0  Held to expiration. No managed exit on the parent ZEBRA. The structure earns its expected payoff at expiry; closing early forfeits the gamma-driven excess return that compounds in the final weeks.\
\'95  \b Long-put overlay at entry (VALIDATED, regime-conditional).\b0  Every ZEBRA position is paired at entry with a single long put on the same underlying, sharing the parent ZEBRA's expiration. Both legs are held to OpEx. Phase 1 backtest (934 cycles, tier-1 cohort) validated a 10%-OTM put as a structural lift over bare ZEBRA: +$9.50/cycle cohort mean, 4/4 walk-forward splits positive. Phase 2 strike-grid sweep then revealed the strike choice is regime-conditional: the pooled-mean winner (deep OTM) is a bull-regime artifact; in the 2022-2024 bear window the ranking inverts and ITM strikes deliver +$15-20/cycle of additional lift over OTM. The operational rule:\
\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'95  \b Stage 1-2 (bull, cascade rings green):\b0  10-15% OTM put. Cheap insurance, 4/4 splits positive, current default.\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'95  \b Stage 3 (fragile, any cascade ring yellow):\b0  ATM put. Only strike that delivered positive or zero lift in every walk-forward split; splits the cost/protection trade-off.\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\'95  \b Stage 4-5 (bear gate open):\b0  strike depends on the active-drawdown qualifier. \b If SPY has made a new 60-day low within the past 30 days\b0  (active-deepening bear): \b 5% ITM put.\b0  Captures the 2022-style drawdown lift. \b If the bear gate is open but SPY has NOT made a new 60-day low in the past 30 days\b0  (troughing / unwinding): \b 10% OTM put\b0  \'97 the underlying is moving up off the trough and ITM puts decay against the move. Intra-bear stability testing on the 2022-2024 window showed ITM5 lift +$49/cyc in 2022 (active deepening) but \'96$9/cyc in 2023 and \'96$9/cyc in 2024 (unwinding/recovery), making the active-drawdown qualifier the operationally important split.\
\
\'a0\'a0\'a0Capital outlay per overlay rises 3-4\'d7 across the OTM\uc0\u8594 ITM transition; sizing must hold the ZEBRA per-position budget within the capital-outlay allocation (see Position Sizing). Split-expiry overlays (put expiring before the parent ZEBRA) are NOT used going forward \'97 the matched-expiry held-to-OpEx geometry is what was validated.\
\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\b Managed-exit variants on the put (ALL REJECTED).\b0  Phase 2 tested five distinct exit criteria on the put leg \'97 close at T-30, T-21, T-14, at 50% gain, at 100% gain. All five variants underperformed held-to-OpEx by $2\'96$6/cycle with 0/4 walk-forward splits showing positive lift. The drag is concentrated in 2021-2023 and 2022-2024 (\'96$20 to \'96$31/cyc) \'97 exactly the windows where the put is supposed to pay off. The credit-spread T-21 discipline does NOT generalize to long-vol legs. Closing the put on any criterion forfeits the late-cycle gamma kick.\
\
\'a0\'a0\'a0\b Conditional-trigger variants (ALL REJECTED vs HOLD).\b0  Phase 2 tested three on-signal triggers \'97 C1 attach-on-drawdown (\'96$3.44 vs HOLD, 0/4), C2 attach-on-term-inversion (\'96$1.21 vs HOLD, 2/4, fires 85% so nearly always-on), C3 attach-on-breadth-divergence (NEVER FIRED in 13 years at the 2026-05-11 thresholds). C4 (30Y > 5%) data-blocked, not yet tested. The "always-on" baseline is structurally robust \'97 trying to gate the overlay on a signal costs more than the saved premium.\
\
\'a0\'a0\'a0Detail: project_zebra_overlay_phase2_complete.md.\
\'95  \b Sizing.\b0  Capital-outlay-based, NOT per-contract. See Position Sizing section. Single AMZN/GOOGL contracts can carry $50K\'96$70K of capital outlay; SPY/QQQ contracts are roughly $7K\'96$10K each. Sizing must be aligned to book equity, not to a per-contract target. The overlay's cost is part of the per-position capital outlay and scales with the regime-conditional strike (deepest in Stage 4-5).\
\'95  \b Execution.\b0  Open all four legs (2\'d7 long ITM call + 1\'d7 short ATM call + 1\'d7 long put per the regime rule) simultaneously on a single combo ticket where the broker supports it; otherwise the parent ZEBRA combo first, then the overlay leg as an immediate follow-on. Slip sensitivity is minimal (slip=0.25 vs 0.50 differs by <$0.05/share on cohort means).\
\
