\b Macro\b0\
\
\'95  \b Favorable.\b0  Bullish trend regimes \'97 the gamma capture mechanism amplifies returns when underlyings rally. 2023-2026 validation window was uniformly stronger than 2013-2022 train across all top names.\
\'95  \b Neutral.\b0  Sideways/flat regimes \'97 the zero-theta property protects the position from time bleed. Flat-day mean MTM change was +$0.58/day across the cohort \'97 sideways stocks slightly grow the position rather than shrink it.\
\'95  \b Unfavorable.\b0  Sustained crash regimes \'97 ZEBRA absorbs full debit loss when spot expires below the long-call strikes. Defined-risk floor holds (max loss = debit), but the loss is real. In contrast to long stock the loss is capped at ~21% of equivalent share-purchase capital, but per-contract dollar damage on high-priced names (AMZN \'96$726, GOOGL \'96$654, TSLA \'96$565) is large \'97 sizing matters.\
