\f0\b\fs28 Covered Call (Credit ETFs) \'97 PROMOTED 2026-04-30, DEMOTED 2026-04-30 on live-execution falsification\

\f1\b0\fs24 \b ⚠ STRATEGY NOT TRADEABLE.\b0  Backtest validated BKLN / JNK / HYG at slip=0.05 mid (mean +7.7% / +7.2% / +4.1% annualized) and walk-forward stable across four 4-year windows. Same-day live attempts on the May 2026 chain falsified the execution premise: \b OTM calls on all three names showed $0 bids with no takers at limit prices \uc0\u8804  mid \'96 $0.125\b0 . Realistic slip is at least $0.30 below mid, which flips the strategy negative on every name. The 13-year backtest P&L history is operationally inviable. COHORT_COVERED_CALL set to empty list in gate_config.py; qualifier no longer emits covered_call verdicts.\
\
The section below is retained as historical research record. The structure mechanics, sizing math, ex-div mechanics, and falsification reasoning are all educationally useful, and the strategy may revive if a different universe (more liquid range-bound names) emerges. The deployment-ready prose below should be read with the falsification banner above held in mind throughout.\
\
Lesson generalized: \b backtest slip assumptions on illiquid option chains are unreliable; live execution is the binding test, not the backtest mean.\b0  See feedback_backtest_slip_assumption_validation.md for the methodology rule that resulted from this falsification.\
