\f0\b\fs24 \i Historical research record (validated by backtest, falsified by live execution):\i0 \

\f1\b0\fs24 Income / yield-enhancement strategy on range-bound credit ETFs whose options market is too thin for credit verticals to extract premium efficiently. Long stock + short OTM call captures monthly dividend distributions and call premium while the stock stays anchored by structural mechanics (floating-rate senior loans for BKLN; high-yield bond mechanics for JNK / HYG). Validated 2026-04-30 across 132 monthly cycles per name 2013-2026; pre-registration sealed in docs/COVERED_CALL_CREDIT_ETFS_PREREG.md. Closes the long-deferred T5 covered-call line from EARNINGS_PREREG.md.\
\
\b Why this is a separate trade family\b0\
\
\'95  The bull_put cohort fails the execution gate on these names \'97 wide bid-ask plus coarse $1 strike spacing means a 30\uc0\u916  OTM put either doesn't exist (BKLN) or carries credit too small to survive realistic slip.\
\'95  The covered call sidesteps this by paying the bid-ask cost ONCE at the call sale (not the round trip a credit vertical pays).\
\'95  Yield-enhancement profile is structurally distinct from premium-selling (bull_put / bear_call), long-vol (inverted fly), and synthetic-stock (ZEBRA) families. Defined-risk by construction: stock cost \'97 premium \'97 dividends is the worst-case loss, realized only if the structural anchor breaks.\
\
\b Structure (VALIDATED)\b0\
\
\'95  Long 100 shares per contract\
\'95  Short 1 call at 30\uc0\u916  closest, expiring next monthly OpEx (\uc0\u8776 21 trading days)\
\'95  Held to expiry; no managed exit; no rolling; no stop-loss\
\'95  Per-cycle P&L per share = (min(S\uc0\u8321 , K) \'96 S\uc0\u8320 ) + premium \'96 slip + dividends_in_window\
\
\b Symbols that respond well (TESTED, VALIDATED at slip=0.05, walk-forward stable across 4 windows 2013-2016 / 2017-2020 / 2021-2024 / 2025-2026)\b0\
\
\'95  \b BKLN\b0  \'97 +7.7% annualized return on capital, 82% win rate, $20\'9623 range for 13 years, ~7% distribution yield. Floating-rate senior loans; near-zero duration risk. Strongest cohort name.\
\'95  \b JNK\b0  \'97 +7.2% annualized, 77% win rate, ~6% yield. High-yield bond ETF.\
\'95  \b HYG\b0  \'97 +4.1% annualized, 70% win rate, ~6% yield. High-yield bond ETF; also bull_put-eligible (cohort name) \'97 covered call vs managed-exit bull_put on HYG is a capital-efficiency choice, not a thesis choice.\
\
\b Symbols that do NOT respond well (TESTED, EXCLUDED)\b0\
\
\'95  \b TLT\b0  \'97 walk-forward FALSIFIED in 2021-2024 (rate-hike crash, mean \'96$0.48/share that window). Long-duration Treasury ETF lacks the floating-rate / par-anchor mechanics that protect BKLN. Don't run TLT covered call until rate volatility settles; revisit in a future regime audit.\
\
\b Why the structural anchor holds\b0\
\
\'95  BKLN: floating-rate senior loans; coupons reset every 30\'9690 days, so duration risk is near zero. Par value barely moves except in genuine credit dislocations.\
\'95  JNK / HYG: high-yield bond ETFs with monthly distributions. Pull toward par value over time.\
\'95  Recovery dynamics: at the COVID March 2020 dislocation, BKLN hit $17.24 intraday and was back over $20 within ~2 weeks. The structural anchor is fast as well as durable. A monthly cycle that started during the dislocation would close fully recovered \'97 which is why the strategy uses no stop-loss rule. Managing a 5% stock decline would crystallize a temporary loss on what's structurally a self-healing instrument.\
\
\b Trade mechanics\b0\
\
\'95  Entry: close on the trading day after prior monthly OpEx. The qualifier fires PENDING from D-3 through entry day, GO on entry day. (See Decision Support Infrastructure for cron timing.)\
\'95  Strike: closest-to-30\uc0\u916  OTM call. On a $1-strike ETF this typically lands at K = round(spot) + 1.\
\'95  Hold: to next monthly OpEx. No managed exit, no rolling.\
\'95  Exit: if S\uc0\u8321  \uc0\u8805  K, stock called away at K and you capture premium + dividends + (K \'96 S\uc0\u8320 ) = max profit per cycle. If S\uc0\u8321  < K, keep stock and capture premium + dividends + (S\uc0\u8321  \'96 S\uc0\u8320 ); next cycle re-arm a new short call against existing stock.\
\'95  Realistic execution: BKLN bid often $0.00 on the call, ask $1.00+. Walk a limit order down patiently; expect $0.20\'960.40 fill on a $0.60 mid. The pre-reg slip=0.05 corresponds to mid-$0.05; slip=0.10 is the pessimistic friction.\
\
\b Ex-div mechanics (the only mid-cycle decision point)\b0\
\
Credit ETFs distribute monthly. If the short call goes ITM near the ex-div date, the call holder will exercise early to capture the dividend, calling away your stock and forfeiting the dividend you'd otherwise collect.\
\
Mitigation. Close the short call before ex-div if it's ITM. Closing cost = remaining premium of the short call. If that's less than the upcoming dividend amount, closing is +EV. The daily alert EX-DIV ASSIGNMENT RISK section fires from D-3 through ex-div day when an open covered_call position has spot ITM or within 1% of strike (see Decision Support Infrastructure).\
\
\b Sizing\b0\
\
Capital-outlay-based, NOT per-contract. Like ZEBRA, covered call doesn't fit the dollar-risk-cap framework because the constraint is upfront capital tied up. See Position Sizing section for full rules.\
\
\b Pending investigations\b0\
\
\'95  Live execution test: realistic limit-order fills on BKLN at the $0.20\'960.40 range vs the backtest assumption of mid \'96 0.05. The backtest assumes patient limit-order discipline; verify on first paper trade.\
\'95  Annual dividend rate refresh: the 2013-2026 backtest captures one specific yield regime. Distribution rate changes will alter the annualized-return calculation; re-run scorecard annually.\
\'95  TLT in a stable-rate regime: the 2021-2024 falsification was a rate-hike artifact. If a future window shows the rate cycle stabilized, revisit the TLT exclusion.\
