\f0\b\fs28 Earnings Plays (Tested 2026-04-25)\

\f1\b0\fs24 A separate trade family from the OpEx-anchored book. The 2026-04-24 bias scan established directional priors on stock prices; the 2026-04-25 structure-level backtest converted those priors into option-structure P&L tests. \b One cohort-level rule promotes (T1: bull put on bias-up names, held to expiration).\b0  Two single-name additions also promote. T2 and T4 cohort-level treatments remain non-tradeable per the test outcomes.\
\
\b Why we run this track\b0\
\
\'95  Earnings dates are calendar-known and create bimodal moves \'97 a fundamentally different driver than OpEx pinning, with overlapping short-premium edge mechanics.\
\'95  Post-announcement IV crush is well-documented: implied volatility typically collapses from its earnings-day peak within 24 hours, regardless of direction.\
\'95  Different calendar driver, often non-overlapping underlying selection, deploys capital in weeks where neither OpEx window is active.\
\'95  Defined-risk only per user policy. No naked short strangles, naked short straddles, or unhedged naked puts into earnings.\
\
