\f0\b\fs28 Management & Exit\

\f1\b0\fs24 \i Scope: management and exit rules for bull_put and bear_call only. Inverted fly management (50%-profit target, held-to-expiration otherwise, no time stop) appears in the Inverted Fly section above. ZEBRA management (held to expiration, no managed exit) appears in the ZEBRA section above. Iron condors and iron flies were tested and rejected; see What Doesn't Work.\i0\
\
\b Exit rules\b0\
\
\'95  \b Window A (45-DTE managed):\b0  first-trigger close on either (a) 50% of max profit reached or (b) DTE <= 21. Whichever comes first. Applies to both bull_put and bear_call.\
\'95  \b Window B (near-OpEx T-5 entry):\b0  held to expiration. No early exit. Tested in Phase 2c and Phase 2d/e \'97 T-3 exit rule hurts 7 of 8 premium-seller structures.\
\'95  Mid-cycle profit-taking outside these rules is not validated. TastyTrade first-trigger management mildly hurts bull_put at slip=0.25 compared with 50%-only exit, but is the conservative default.\
\
\b Rolling \'97 bull_put (validated in Phase 2g)\b0\
\
\'95  \b Trigger:\b0  mark-to-market loss >= 1x entry credit\
\'95  \b Style:\b0  down-and-out. Close the losing position; open a fresh bull_put at the new max-pain strike on the next monthly OpEx\
\'95  \b Credit requirement:\b0  the roll must open for a net credit. If not, accept the loss and do not roll\
\'95  \b Cap:\b0  one roll per original cycle. Serial rolling is untested and not permitted\
\'95  \b Per-name selectivity:\b0  SPX, WMT, DIA, VNQ, QQQ, TLT, SPY benefit from rolling. XLU, IYR, XLV, KO do NOT \'97 hold to expiry on these names\
\'95  Do NOT apply the contango+VRP>0 rule at the trigger day. The entry filter helps at entry; at trigger day it selects against rollable cycles\
\'95  Do NOT use spot-based stops. Short puts mean-revert enough that intraweek breach is not a reliable kill signal\
\
\b Rolling \'97 bear_call (tested H3 2026-04-24: FALSIFIED)\b0\
\
\'95  Do NOT roll bear_call positions. Hold to expiry per Window A / Window B rules.\
\'95  H3 test on 125 triggered cycles: unconditional roll produced combined mean -$0.946 vs accept-loss baseline -$0.855. Rolling compounds losses.\
\'95  Only 29.6% of rolls improved the outcome. Even regime-gated rolling (SPY < 200dma at entry) gave only a tiny +$0.018 lift on a small sample.\
\'95  Mechanism: bear_call up-and-out rolls require spot > MP again at T-5 entry, which in a persistent bull means opening another ITM position against the trend.\
\
\b Stops that do not work (tested and rejected)\b0\
\
\'95  \b T-3 exit rule:\b0  hurts 7 of 8 premium-seller structures. Theta harvest lives in the final 2 days.\
\'95  \b MTM-based mid-cycle stop\b0  (close if MTM <= 0 on Tuesday): 76.8% of red-Tuesday cycles recover by expiry.\
\'95  \b Spot-based stop\b0  (close if spot breaches short strike): crystallizes losses that would have reverted.\
\
\b Expected trigger frequencies\b0\
\
\'95  50% profit trigger on bull_put: fires early on roughly 30-40% of cycles\
\'95  21-DTE trigger: fires on the remainder, roughly 60-70% of cycles\
\'95  MTM roll trigger on bull_put_mp: fires on roughly 34% of cycles (Phase 2g)\
